dbt-build [-s SELECTOR] [-n] [-- EXTRA_ARGS...]

Run `dbt build` locally with --defer against the production
ref-state manifest, writing results to your personal dataset. Unlike
dbt-run, this also seeds, tests, and snapshots — anything `dbt build`
covers.

Omit -s to open an fzf picker over all dbt models AND seeds. Recently
selected nodes appear at the top with a "last run X ago" label. The node
list is cached in ~/.cache/dbt-build/nodes.txt; select the REFRESH entry
in the picker to re-run dbt ls and refresh the cache.

  -s SELECTOR   dbt node selector; skips the fzf picker
  -n, --list    dry-run: show which nodes will be built locally vs read from
                prod (via --defer), then exit without running dbt
  --            pass any additional arguments straight to dbt
  -h, --help    show this help

The ref-state manifest must exist at $DBT_STATE_DIR/manifest.json and be no
older than 7 days. Run dbt-sync-state to refresh it.

The cost estimate only covers models (seeds don't dry-run via bq).

ENVIRONMENT (all required, set in ~/.zshrc.thismachine)
  DBT_STATE_DIR      path to dir containing the ref-state manifest.json
  DBT_PROJECT_SUBDIR subdir of the git root containing dbt_project.yml
  DBT_TARGET         dbt target name (e.g. local_dev)
  DBT_DEV_PROJECT    GCP project ID used for local runs
  DBT_DATASET_PREFIX BigQuery dataset name for locally-built models

Examples:
  dbt-build
  dbt-build -s my_seed
  dbt-build -s my_model+
  dbt-build -n -s my_model+
  dbt-build -s tag:finance -- --full-refresh
